Down Periscope is a 1996 comedy film starring Kelsey Grammer as the captain of a rust-bucket Navy submarine, the USS Stingray, who is fighting for his career as he is saddled with a group of misfit seamen.David S. Ward directed the film. Lauren Holly and Rob Schneider co-star as officers on the sub. Also featured are Harry Dean Stanton, Bruce Dern, William H. Macy and Rip Torn.The name of the film is a play on the 1959 World War II drama Up Periscope, takes plot themes — such as a decrepit submarine and female crewmember(s) — from the 1959 World War II comedy Operation Petticoat, and spoofs several titles in the genre of films about submarines including Cold War drama The Hunt for Red October.
